title: Police: 2 women arrested after fight on JetBlue flight
text: Travel Links Yesterday's Places NEW YORK (AP) -- Two women have been arrested after police say they attacked each other as their flight arrived at New York's Kennedy Airport from Jamaica. Port Authority spokesman Joe Pentangelo (pehn-TAN'-jeh-loh) says it happened at 8:45 a.m. Wednesday. The dispute started after a 61-year-old passenger at a window seat tried to climb over another woman as Jet Blue Flight 960 approached the gate. The older woman used an eyebrow razor to slash the 52-year-old woman and a man who tried to intervene. The younger woman then used pepper-spray on the knife-wielding passenger. Seven passengers were treated for difficulty breathing. Police say the 61-year-old was arrested on assault and weapons charges. The other woman was arrested for possessing pepper spray.
